**Overall Meaning:**

This verse highlights the profound knowledge gained by understanding the divine presence interwoven into the seasons (vairājaṁ ṛtuṣu protam).  Those who possess this knowledge radiate with divine brilliance (virājati) and are blessed with abundant progeny, livestock, and the brilliance of Brahman (brahmavarcasena).  They are blessed with a long life, abundant progeny, livestock, and great fame.  They are in tune with the natural rhythms and are never criticized because they embody the divine principle of the seasons (artūn). 

The verse emphasizes the transformative power of knowledge, highlighting the ability to live in harmony with the natural world and achieve a life of prosperity and abundance.  It emphasizes that this knowledge is a gift from the divine, leading to a life of radiance and fulfillment. 
